Game Database Explorer

A web application that allows users to explore video game data using the RAWG video game database API. The project demonstrates building a modern frontend application using React, TypeScript, and REST APIs.

The application fetches game data dynamically and renders it using reusable React components in a responsive interface.

Live Demo

https://jsanc189.github.io/Game-Database-Explorer/

Features

- Fetches real video game data from the RAWG REST API
- Displays game information such as titles, ratings, and release dates
- Dynamically renders game data using React components
- Clean and modular component structure
- Responsive layout for different screen sizes
- Automatic deployment through GitHub Actions

Technologies Used

React

- TypeScript
- Vite
- REST APIs
- HTML5
- CSS3
