How It Works

The application sends requests to the RAWG API.
- Game data is returned in JSON format.
- TypeScript interfaces define the structure of the API responses.
- React components iterate through the data and render game cards.
- The site is built with Vite and deployed automatically to GitHub Pages using a GitHub Actions workflow.

Local Development

Clone the repository:

- git clone https://github.com/jsanc189/Game-Database-Explorer.git

Navigate into the project:

- cd Game-Database-Explorer

Install dependencies:

- npm install

Run the development server:

- npm run dev

The site will be available at:

- http://localhost:5173
- Build for Production
- npm run build

This generates the production build in the dist directory.

Deployment

- The project deploys automatically using GitHub Actions when code is pushed to the main branch. The workflow builds the project and publishes the dist folder to GitHub Pages.

